\begin_layout Standard
By the convolution definition we get:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f\left(t\right)*g\left(t\right)=\stackrel[-\infty]{\infty}{\int}f\left(x\right)g\left(t-x\right)dx=h\left(t\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Lets denote 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(t-1\right)=a\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $g\left(t+1\right)=b\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

 and we get:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
a\left(t\right)*b\left(t\right)=\stackrel[-\infty]{\infty}{\int}a\left(x\right)*b\left(t-x\right)dx=\stackrel[-\infty]{\infty}{\int}f\left(x-1\right)g\left(t-x+1\right)dx
\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula 
\[
=\stackrel[-\infty]{\infty}{\int}f\left(x-1\right)g\left(t-(x-1)\right)dx=_{\left(1\right)}\stackrel[-\infty]{\infty}{\int}f\left(l\right)g\left(t-l\right)dl=h\left(l\right)
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Explanation to 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(1\right)$
\end_inset

: change of variable: 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(x-1\right)=l$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
And we get the 
\begin_inset Formula $f\left(t-1\right)*g\left(t+1\right)=h\left(t\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

